tl;dr: instead of every client hitting the ipfs then making dozens or more calls to @infura_io and @graphprotocol ($$$), one client every few minutes makes those calls and caches the results on @pinatacloud. every client in between gets cached data from pinata (fast+cheap).

to create a performant and decentr. dapp frontend w/ fresh data, visitors first fetch the most recently pinned cached data from @pinatacloud on ipfs. if the data is more than a few mins old, the client fetches new data from @graphprotocol & @infura_io, then pins it anew to pinata

ipfs hosted decentralized websites struggle to achieve the performance of centralized sites running on AWS/Vercel because all the cool realtime data must be fetched from @infura_io and @graphprotocol by each client each time they load the page. this is slow and $$$.
